{
  "texts": [
    "Suppose we have defined R z 1,...,z k i 0,i 1,...,i k-1 and Q z 1,...,z k i 0,...,i k for k ≥ 2, i 0,..., i k ∈ {0,..., K -1} and z 1,..., z k ∈ Ref.",
    "We letR z 1,...,z k+1 i 0,i 1,...,i k = R(Q z 1,...,z k i 0,...,i k, z k+1); Q z 1,...,z k+1 i 0,...,i k+1 = Q(R z 1,...,z k+1i 0,i 1,...,i k, i k+1), for z k+1 ∈ Ref and i k+1 ∈ {0,..., K -1}.",
    "Geometrically, Q i 0 's naturally partition R 0 into subcubes.",
    "Each subcube Q i 0 contains a rescaled and translated copy of the reference latticeRef(Q i 0) = 1 K Ref+p(Q i 0).",
    "Each point z ∈ Ref(Q i 0) is a principal vertex of one of the rectangles R(Q i 0, z 1) = R z 1 i 0."
  ]
}